column5: Never know who may help themselves when you're not around.....
HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHA, that's priceless Wayne.  Too bad TJ has no taste in beer  Joey
A beautiful place to sit and have a picnic.. and drink someone else's beer! LOL....... Seriously... I was flying.. it was an empty can! (after Leah finished it!)
Thanks goodness you had those shorts on....     Oh... you had a shirt and socks on??? Nice camo.
That is one of those PRICELESS pics.

funny stuff  is that a little creek to the left of the picture and is that weeds coming out from it or a sand shelf from the current.... I never get to see water from that angle...looks like you can tell a lot from shots like that

Stinkin Air Vagrants....  swooping down and swapping good ole Carling, with Heineken SWILL.  Those are great pictures, the Aerial View is awesome!!!  Are those fro the first time, or have you been back bumming beer since..lol

Flight school ...$20000 Flight hours to get pilots license... $15000 Owning and flying your own float plane... $180000  Landing on a remote lake and "borrowing" a 75 cent beer from a root admin and then posting the photo on the board... PRICELESS!!!       Disclaimer: All figures (including the beer) are completely made-up and may not reflect true market value.
LOL... Its a buck a beer..... hmmfff!!!!
....Like Kickingfrog said...."Priceless".
Never mind the decoy beer is the 1,000,000.02 in cash and gold bars still hidden in the mattress?
I agree, that's way past priceless! I might be seeing the vagrant and his sidekick tomorrow.....my beer is safe though cause he'll be arriving in a land vehicle and won't be able to sneak in.
That's GREAT!!!     Awesome aerial shot Wayne.
Truly priceless!! Thanks for a good funny post for my early afternoon read.
:lol:  :lol:  That's Hilarious!

Wayne...where is your fishing rod ????...or you could just go fishin,from the plane..  ..trolling ceasna style !!!!.  ..great shots from the skycam too !!!...glad to see you back on the board wayne..  ..cheers
I'm sure you could find a SAM on ebay TJ
Nice job Wayne.   I love it.

TJ... from first and only time up. Was an empty can from your campfire pit! LOL We'll get up again next season for sure. Nice spot to shoot a landing over the downstream rapids!  ...and yes Terry... looks like a creek.. sand bar and weed bed.
now that's funny...nice shots from the air
